/** \mainpage Userguide

ZZAVNAD allows the user to view S-parameter files derived from nanoVNA.
It provides the following functionality:
- Connects to a nanoVNA using a serial USB port.
- Controls the nanoVNA to obtain scan data.
- Reads and writes captured data to filestore.
- Runs through the calibration process and can save calibration data 
to filestore.
- Displays upto 8 sets of scanned data in one plot.
- Displays the data in a number of formats:
  - In the frequency domain: eg SWR or Resistance/Reactance.
  - In the time domain: Time-domain reflectometry.
  - Scatter diagrams: Smith chart, Resistance vs Reactance.
- Allows the plots to be easily zoomed and scrolled.

\section contents contents

